<event name="TURBAN_BOMBING">
	<text>As you begin to leave, you catch sight of a shooting star in the sky. Quite strange, considering it's not night time... Then it dawns on you what this is, just in time for you to take cover as a missile barrage strikes one of the nearby towers and sends it crashing down. The attack is followed by a flurry of more missile strikes as Theocracy and Coalition Bombers begin to jump in. The city is under attack!</text>
	<resetFtl/>   
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Get back to your ship and flee as soon as possible.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You take off at once, but you aren't fast enough to escape unharmed. A missile strikes your engines, damaging them badly, while a Coalition Elite spots you and engages!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_COALITION_ELITE_FIGHT" hostile="true"/>
			<damage amount="3" system="engines" effect="breach"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>계속...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Stay and try to aid the other civilians.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You came here to save the Federation, but what good is that if you abandon everyone else on your path in doing so? You help pull several civilians out from beneath collapsed debris, but after a missile strike almost costs you your life, you realize if you stay on the surface any longer you'll die. Fortunately, a strangely dressed Rockman in worn priest clothing motions for you to follow him. "Come with me, quickly! We must get to the sewers, we'll be safe from the bombardement there."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Retreat into the sewers.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You trek through the sewers in silence with your crew, following the Rockman and his lantern through the labyrinth beneath the streets. Eventually, he breaks the silence. "You are noble to stay and help these people. There are few who would. Come, not much further now until we reach the sanctuary." True to his word, only a few turns later and you arrive at a crudely constructed door which you slide out of the way. A repugnant smell assaults your senses but you stifle the urge to gag and take a seat next to a sleeping outcast.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>계속...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The people in the room pay you little attention, but your companion draws many nasty looks. "Turns out you are a bad omen, Argo. We were warned of your curse, and now look where we are. We should never have given you asylum", spits a young female Mantis with a blood-soaked bandana over her left eye. This insult is met by murmurs of agreement by the rest of the room, who turn their backs to Argo. In defeat, he stumbles over to where you are.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Why is everyone mad at you?</text>
								<event>
									<text>Argo sighs and slumps back, pulling a small canteen from his belt and taking a sip. "Not long ago, I was in nothing but the highest graces of the Theocracy. My father sat at the table of victors when the Elders divided the Rock-Crystal Empire and seized power, but he was denied a place as an Elder. He warned me that the Elders would not be kind to our heritage unless we continued to prove our loyalty. I served as a Chrysolic priest for many years before I married my wife, Iri. Together we had two children, a son and a daughter."</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>계속...</text>
										<event>
											<text>"We both knew that neither of their lives would be easy, but we tried as hard as possible to place them in positions of security. Our son was sent to the Inquisition to be trained as a Crusader, while our daughter was promised a hand in marriage with Toarde, the head Elder. She was but a young child at the time, but what were we to do? The Rock people hated us, they saw us as exactly what we were. My daughter hated me too, and one day she simply vanished from her room in Toarde's palace along with her brother. Toarde was furious, and he blamed me because he had no one else to blame."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>계속...</text>
												<event>
													<text>"I was exiled from the Theocracy and abandoned by my wife, who chose to pledge herself to Toarde instead. With nowhere to go I traveled to the Badlands, where I found Turban. The outcasts who lived here hated me, but I was able to survive by proving my usefulness as a guide through the unexplored halls of the buildings. I had helped in the planning for the original construction of Turban before it was abandoned, you see. After the outcasts had established full control I was allowed to stay, but they began to call me the 'cursed one'. A homeless prophet who wandered the streets claimed that I would bring destruction to this place. And... well, here we are I suppose."</text>
													<choice hidden="true">
														<text>계속...</text>
														<event>
															<text>Argo falls silent, staring at the floor. He sheathes his canteen and the room turns silent once again.</text>
															<choice hidden="true">
																<text>Continue to sit in silence.</text>
																<event load="TURBAN_BOMBING_COALITION"/>
															</choice>
														</event>
													</choice>
												</event>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue to sit in silence.</text>
								<event load="TURBAN_BOMBING_COALITION"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
        </event>
